# Push changes to GitHub

When you complete substantive edits in this repo (code, migrations the user cares about, config that should be versioned):

1. Run `git status`, stage the relevant files, and commit with a clear message.
2. Push to the current branch (usually `main`) on `origin` — e.g. `git push origin main`.
3. Do this in the same session as the edits; do not leave fixes only local unless the user explicitly asks not to push or not to commit.

If push fails (auth, conflicts), fix or report and retry; do not assume the user will push manually.
